  "e9a0e431-3761-7b4c-86cf-af31c0b7383c"],
 " icon in the top left corner under Assistance. You can also press the F1 \
key and it will bring you to the documentation home page. If you highlight \
over text and press the F1 key, it will search the Mathematica documentation \
for your highlighted text. If you are ever unsure of how to do something in \
Mathematica, check the documentation. If that doesn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t work, \
searching online can also help as there is a widespread community of \
Mathematica users. "
}], "Text",
