Cell["\<\
Another useful notation is postfix notation (//). This notation tells \
Mathematica to apply a command after evaluating everything else first. There \
are a few common instances where I use post fixing myself:

For numerical outputs:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.977502248850111*^9, 3.9775022509693184`*^9}, {
