 "For this section, you will want to ensure Dynamic Updating is enabled, see \
Section 0 for instructions on how to do this.  You have probably used or seen \
WolframA|lpha to help with homework from time to time. If you have Dynamic \
Updating enabled, you can access the WolframAlpha directly in Mathematica. \
You can open a Wolfram|Alpha prompt by pressing \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Ctrl + \
=\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] in an input cell this will cause a dialog box to \
appear with an orange equals sign: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  GraphicsBox[
   TagBox[RasterBox[CompressedData["
